n for producing and exhibiting avant-garde films, through its transformation into a commercial-industrial enterprise, and into its final decline as a show business management style suppressed many of its voices. The first book to highlight the work of Hofsess, an innovative filmmaker whose critical role in the MFB has been almost entirely eclipsed by Reitman’s legend, Hamilton Babylon is a fascinating study of the tension between art and business in the growth of the Canadian film industry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aExperimental filmszOntariozHamiltonxHistory and criticism. 0aMotion picturesxProduction and directionzOntariozHamiltonxHistory. 0aMotion pictureszOntariozHamiltonxHistory. 0aMotion pictures, CanadianzOntariozHamiltonxHistory. 7aART / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311066595640uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266918540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442669185423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442669185.jpg  a978-3-11-066595-6  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles